user.about:
Roomerang is an end-to-end short stays team based in Melbourne.

We are avid travellers and know how hard it can be to find comfortable and cosy, yet affordable accommodation. We try to remove all the complications surrounding your stay, so you can focus on other important aspects of your trip. And if you feel we have left anything out, let us know and we would love to help.

Roomerang provides professionally cleaned and well-kept, affordable stays presenting you with a home to return to no matter who you are, where you're from or what you are here for!

co_host.description:
Our newly built and luxurious, 2 bedroom apartment, MARCO, will allow you to experience Melbourne at its finest and fullest. Overlook the Albert Park Lake and Sea right from the balcony of this cosy apartment. You will also find yourself near the bustling CBD, Southbank Promenade, Garden and Arts Precinct, and Crown Casino. With easy access to the city via public transport around the area, hurry and make this place your first step in exploring all that Melbourne has to offer.

The apartment is inspired by Scandinavian interior design, with the living room featuring a dining table, TV, coffee table, a cozy sofa and a fully equip open-concept kitchen for you to cook up a meal. Separate from the living room is an open balcony with a gorgeous view. 

Linen and blanket for the sofabed will only be provided upon request. The request for sofabed will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check in. Last minute requests for sofa bed linen will incur an additional surcharge of $30.

Two bedrooms contain beautifully styled Queen bed and Single bed with clean and luxurious linen to keep you comfortable during your stay. Upon arrival, you will also find the bathroom stocked with body wash, hand soap, shampoo, conditioner, toilet paper and fresh bath towels. A washing machine and dryer is also available for guests to use.

Free WiFi will be available throughout your stay, which will be detailed in the manual provided.

Guest will have access to the entire home and parking if available on-site.

[Check-in]
- CHECK-IN: Standard check-in is between 3-9pm. 
- Check-ins between 9pm-midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $25. 
-Check-ins after midnight will incur a late check-in fee of $50.
*We will require you to present a valid photo ID matching the booking at the time of check-in.*

[Check-out]
- CHECK-OUT: Check-out is strictly by 10 am (LATE CHECK-OUTs WILL INCUR A FEE OF $100).

Once your booking has been confirmed, our housing manual will be sent to your email address, containing all information related to your booking. Please refer to that for check-in and check-out instructions.

Ongoing communication is best via the platform or through the phone number provided. Please provide us with your name and reservation address if you do call us, and we'll be at your assistance.

Located a short distance away from the city, you will find yourself near the Southbank Promenade, Crown Casino, National Gallery of Victoria, Arts Centre, Queen Victoria Gardens and Sea Life Melbourne Aquarium. There are also multiple restaurant options located near the apartment.

Trams on City Road are located 200m away.

[Excess Rubbish]
Please dispose of excess rubbish in the rubbish chute located near the lift.

[Strict House Rules]
- No smoking or drug use allowed (violation will incur a $500 fine).
- No parties allowed.
- No pets allowed.
- The correct number of guests staying must be reflected in the booking. Linen and towels will only be provided for the number of guests included in the booking. 
- Please leave the property in a similar condition as it was during check-in. 
- Breakages, damages, theft and loss will be the guest's liability and responsibility.
- Violation of any of the rules will result in a loss of your security deposit and/or additional charges.
- As part of our verification procedure, a photo of a government-issued ID and a selfie may be requested.
- Noise levels are to be kept at an appropriate level at all times.
- Please dispose of excess rubbish according to the rubbish disposal instructions located in the Housing Manual.
- PLEASE USE THE RANGE HOOD WHEN COOKING so as to not set off the smoke alarm. If the smoke alarm goes off, DO NOT OPEN THE FRONT DOOR. Doing so will cause the fire truck to come to the apartment in which you will be fined heavily (approx. $1,500).
- We provide a set of toiletries to ensure you are settled in well for the initial period of your stay. Regrettably, we are unable to provide re-stocks or refills of these toiletries if you have a longer stay. You may, however, request for housekeeping during your stay at additional cost.

[LOST & FOUND]
-Lost items will be kept in our office for 1 week. $50 will be charged for postage to mail the item back to you upon request.
